Prove (3.31)
by showing the RHS is equivalent to the LHS

Proof:
  (p ⋁ q) ⋁ (p ⋁ r)
=    〈 Associativity of ⋁ 〉
  p ⋁ (q ⋁ p) ⋁ r
=    〈 Symmetry of ⋁ 〉
  p ⋁ (p ⋁ q) ⋁ r
=    〈 Associativity of ⋁ 〉
  (p ⋁ p) ⋁ (q ⋁ r)
=    〈 Idempotency of ⋁ 〉
  p ⋁ (q ⋁ r)  ╱╱

------------------------------

Prove (3.32)
by showing the RHS is equivalent to the LHS

Proof:
  p ⋁ q ≡ p ⋁ ¬q
=    〈 Distributivity of ⋁ over ≡ 〉
  p ⋁ (q ≡ ¬q)
=    〈 (3.15) p ≡ ¬p ≡ false 〉
  p ⋁ false
=    〈 Identity of ⋁ 〉
  p  ╱╱

------------------------------

Prove (3.36)
by showing the LHS is equivalent to the RHS

Proof:
  p ⋀ q
=    〈 golden rule 〉
  p ≡ q ≡ p ⋁ q
=    〈 Symmetry of ≡ 〉
  q ≡ p ≡ p ⋁ q
=    〈 Symmetry of ⋁ 〉
  q ≡ p ≡ q ⋁ p
=    〈 golden rule 〉
  q ⋀ p  ╱╱

------------------------------

Prove (3.38)
by showing equivalence to previous theorem

Proof:
  p ⋀ p ≡ p
=    〈 golden rule with q ≔ p 〉
  p ⋁ p ≡ p
=    〈 Idempotency of ⋁ 〉
  true  ╱╱

------------------------------

Prove (3.47a)
by showing the LHS is equivalent to the RHS

Proof:
  ¬(p ⋀ q)
=    〈 Golden rule 〉
  ¬(p ≡ q ≡ p ⋁ q)
=    〈 Distributivity of ¬ over ≡ 〉
  ¬p ≡ q ≡ p ⋁ q
=    〈 (3.32) with p, q ≔ q, p 〉
  ¬p ≡ p ⋁ ¬q
=    〈 (3.32) with p, q ≔ ¬p, q 〉
  ¬p ⋁ ¬q  ╱╱

------------------------------

Prove (3.47b)
by showing the LHS is equivalent to the RHS

Proof:
  ¬(p ⋁ q)
=    〈 Double negation, twice 〉
  ¬(¬¬p ⋁ ¬¬q)
=    〈 De Morgan, (3.47a) with p, q ≔ ¬p, ¬q 〉
  ¬¬(¬p ⋀ ¬q)
=    〈 Double negation 〉
  ¬p ⋀ ¬q  ╱╱
